Entries.default: "Fresh fruit, vegetables, dried goods for long voyages. I got it all, right here!"
"A repeat customer. I like your type."
"What can I stock you up with today?"
"Do you have any unripened palm stones?"
"Show me what you have for sale."
" 'Course I do. But they're no good to eat when they're not ripe. Will make you sick so long as they're purple, aye?" She strokes her chin.
"Tell you what, though - I'll still sell you what I got. Just don't eat them till they're brown."
